release.notes:
"RSD Exclusive" release, issued in a gatefold sleeve with single sided 11.5"x11.5" insert with liner notes.

The US Record Store Day website states that this release was released in a quantity of 5,000 copies.

[Hype Sticker]
- Record Store Day exclusive
- 2-LP expanded edition on limited-edition pink vinyl
- Includes the original 1981 album plus a bonus LP of rare remixes and new liner notes by Chris Franz and Tina Weymouth
- Features the timeless classics "Genius Of Love" and "Wordy Rappinghood"
- RCV1 706343 / 603497834914

[Tracks]
- A1 to B4 from the original 1981 release.
- C1 & C2 from [r=128268] (Sire 49817).
- C3 from [r=76877] (Sire PRO-A-996).
- D1 to D3 from [r=107476] (Sire 29930).

[Runouts]
- Laser etched runouts read clockwise with the labels, i.e. "252899E1 1405342 MRP4308/RCV1-706343/603497837914-A".
- Hand etched runouts and stamped "STERLING" read counter-clockwise away from the label, i.e. "JN-H STERLING 1#  ̶R̶1̶ ̶ RCV1-706343-A (1)".
